                    While a UK Private Limited Company (LTD) is no longer legally required to appoint an individual **Company Secretary** under the Companies Act 2006, the corporate duties and strict filing requirements remain mandatory. The director of the company is legally responsible for these compliance activities, which can become overwhelming.
